        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/c68b51/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2021-02-01T05:54:51.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Why 2002?  The article itself says \u201cAsk growers for comparisons with other vintages, and they can\u2019t agree. Maybe 2015? Not quite. Or 2009, 2010? They\u2019d be the choice of Guillaume d\u2019Angerville of Domaine Marquis d\u2019Angerville. St\u00e9phane Follin-Arbelet settles instead for 1947, which would floor most of us.\u201d  And others on WB have speculated various combos of 2017 + 2009/2015/2018.</p>",
